                                                                                            <p class="word-copy-lh-mb"><strong>Alonso Rabí Do Carmo</strong> (b. 1964, Lima, Peru) is a writer, journalist, and university professor. He studied literature at the&nbsp;Universidad Nacional Mayor de San Marcos&nbsp;in Lima, Peru, and received his PhD in Spanish at the University of Colorado at Boulder. He has authored several collections of poetry, including <em>Concierto en el subterráneo</em> (1992), <em>Quieto vaho sobre el espejo</em> (1994), <em>En un purísimo ramaje de vacíos</em> (2000), and&nbsp;<em>Meditación sobre el heroísmo y otros textos incompletos</em> (2025).&nbsp;In 2020 he edited the volume <em>El texto literario. Materiales para su estudio</em>.&nbsp;He is also the author of <em>Universo MVLL</em> (2019), <em>Antiguos y nuevos animales literarios</em> (2022), and <em>Prosas minúsculas</em> (2025). He currently teaches Spanish language and literature courses at the University of Lima.</p>
